ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='The unit tests look comprehensive for profile service. They cover cre
ate, update, get, addPhoto, reorderPhotos, deletePhoto, age validation, tag limi
ts, etc.\n\nNow let\'s check if there are any remaining issues in the mobile cod
e regarding design system compliance.\n\n- `ProfileSetupPage` uses `ScaffoldMess
enger.of(context).showSnackBar` with `SnackBar`. This is a Material component, b
ut it\'s for displaying temporary messages. The design docs don\'t explicitly ba
n `SnackBar`, but they ban using native Material components in place of design-s
ystem components for core UI like buttons, text fields, etc. `SnackBar` is more 
of a platform-level feedback widget. We can let it pass, but maybe note it.\n- `
ProfileSetupPage` uses `LinearProgressIndicator` and `showDatePicker`. `LinearPr
ogressIndicator` is Material. `showDatePicker` is Material. The design doc says 
"禁止在 `pages/` 中直接使用原生 Material 组件（如 `TextField`、`ElevatedButton`
、`OutlineInputBorder`）替代 design-system 组件". It specifically lists TextFiel
d, ElevatedButton, OutlineInputBorder. It doesn\'t mention progress indicators o
r date pickers. However, for a rigorous review, using `showDatePicker` directly 
might be acceptable for MVP, but we could note it.\n- `ProfileEditPage` uses `Ci
rcularProgressIndicator`. Again, standard Material.\n- Colors: The pages use `De
signTokens.background`, `DesignTokens.textPrimary`, etc. Good.\n- No hardcoded `
Color(0xFF...)` found.\n\nLet\'s check if the `DesignTokens` class exists and ha
s the properties used.',
    encrypted=None
)
